## Architecture rules
- src/index.js is the production entry point (Wrangler `main`).
- All business logic lives in src/ as focused modules.
- Never hardcode workspace_id, tenant_id, email addresses, or secret values.
- Agent Sam: D1 is canonical operational state; Supabase is the required observability mirror. Full lifecycle, tables, and required end-of-change alignment report: `.cursor/rules/agentsam-d1-supabase-alignment.mdc` (always applied).

## Deploy — never guess (wrong command = wasted work)
- `npm run deploy:full` — DEFAULT. Route map + D1 schema doc + docs ingest + D1 memory ingest (when hashes change) + `deploy-frontend.sh` (clean `npm run build:vite-only`, `bump-cache.js`, R2 sync, Worker) + codebase index + eval + hooks.
- `npm run deploy` — Worker/API only (src/). No R2 upload; does not refresh dashboard assets.
- `./scripts/with-cloudflare-env.sh npx wrangler deploy -c wrangler.production.toml` — Worker-only one-liner.
- `deploy:frontend`, `deploy:full`, and `deploy:full:safe` always run a clean `dashboard/dist` via `npm run build:vite-only`, then `node scripts/bump-cache.js`, then R2 sync. Never set `SKIP_VITE_BUILD` for production paths; the deploy scripts reject it.

## Sandbox is DISCONTINUED
- Never suggest deploy-sandbox.sh or promote-to-prod.sh — both are marked dangerous/discontinued.
- Deploy directly to production with npm run deploy:full.

## Dashboard build rules
- NEVER run cd dashboard
- Always use `npm run build:vite-only` from repo root (never `cd dashboard`).

CF Builds auto-deploys Worker on push to main. Does NOT upload R2 frontend bundle.
Run deploy:full locally when dashboard changes need to be live immediately.
